name: Waiwhetu Sports Centre
description:
We allow WALK INS and BOOKINGS at our vax centre.
During level 2 we are based indoors at the Waiwhetu Fitness Centre located on Te Whiti Park. Limited FREE parking is available outside our centre with overflow parking available within Te Whiti Park and on Riverside Drive. Vehicle access is via Whites Line East at the childrens playround on Te Whiti park.  
Children aged 12-15years are able to have their vaccination if their parents/caregivers have an existing booking at our centre on the day. 
You will need to wait and be observed for 15 minutes after your vaccination.
You must wear a facemask and keep your social distancing of 2meters inside our centre.

DO NOT ATTEND and PLEASE REBOOK If you are... 
Unwell with cold or flu like symptoms, have a sore throat, a cough, a high fever etc.  You have been to any locations of interest, awaiting a COVID test or have been asked to stay home and self isolate.

name: Christchurch Arena Drive Through Site
description:
**Please use the Wrights Road entrance to the stadium car park. You will be directed where to go upon entry.**


*Please note this is a drive in clinic. For your and our safety, pedestrians will not be permitted.*


People being vaccinated must be seated next to a window and their full arm/shoulder must be accessible through the window.
You’ll be asked to queue. You’ll need to park and wait for twenty minutes following your vaccination. Please allow at least 1 hour for the entire process. Bring a book, your knitting and/or your phone charger. 

**You are welcome to bring along any friends and whānau to be vaccinated, you do not need to have a booking to be vaccinated at this site.**
